description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to join the Young People&#39;s Mental Heath Research team at Pennine Care NHS Foundation Trust. Working with National and International leaders in this field, the post holder will be responsible for delivering on a range of studies involving young people with mental health problems. Educated to degree level in a relevant discipline, you will be integral to the development of this unit and pivotal in ensuring it reaches its research goals. The Young People&#39;s Mental Health Research Unit is an innovative collaboration between Pennine Care and its academic partners to deliver young people&#39;s research across this area of Greater Manchester and beyond. You will be based at Trust HQ, but will need a flexible and adaptive approach in order to reach potential research participants across the trust footprint&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameSimon KayeJob titleResearch and Innovation ManagerEmail addresssimon.kaye2@nhs.netTelephone number07775007114&lt;/p&gt;
